com.nokia.places

Interface Contacts


  • public interface Contacts
    This interface represents all the different means of contacting a Place.

    There are multiple ways to contact a place. For each available type of contact, a Contacts object contains an attribute that provides a list of contact details for that type. The possible contact types include:

    • phone - a telephone number for voice calls
    • fax - a telephone number for facsimile (telecopy) transmissions
    • website - a URL for the website operated by the place
    • email - an email address for sending messages to the place


    See Also:
    ContactDetail, Nokia's Restful Places API - Contacts
